      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ULFBERHT (6) looks the one to beat. Two runs to date have both seen him finish second, well backed here on debut to start $1.70 and finding the line nicely before another rock solid effort again at this track last start. Finds a very winnable race third up and should go awfully close. LIBER'S IMPACT (3) has been fair in two runs to date, not far away at Mornington over this trip when last seen. He can kick up from the inside gate and take catching. PRAGUE PRIDE (9) has been thereabouts in two runs to date, the debut effort at Kilmore especially was solid for this. She can land midfield and have last crack. LOCHEND PRINCESS (8) put in a better effort here when last seen at big odds and has claims off that while SHY VELOCITY (5) can run well on debut for the Rae yard off a trial win at Moe.",
